WHAT

A rewrite of the video engine of VTmpeg, a software which plays videos from a queue, from the former Void Technologies.
VTmpeg is divided in two parts:

    VTserver: Creates a window on the display, a UNIX domain socket server and waits for commands.
    VTclient: Connects on VTserver and send commands for managing VTserver queue and state.

REQUIREMENTS TO BUILD

gstreamer 1.0 and gtk 3 development libraries.

Packages on Debian/Ubuntu:
libgtk-3-dev libgstreamer1.0-dev libgstreamer-plugins-base1.0-dev

REQUIREMENTS TO RUN

gtk 3 and gstreamer 1.0 runtime libraries (plugins-good, plugins-bad, plugins-ugly depending on media).
